Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.40,0:00:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.20,0:00:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, one of the twelve disciples...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.54,0:00:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,debt collector, eradicator of magicians, and lowly servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.35,0:00:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.46,0:00:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Angelene! You...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.49,0:00:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.18,0:00:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-T-R, T-T-O-P, A-O.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.57,0:00:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was sloppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.06,0:00:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't pay much attention to the exterior,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was easy to interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.62,0:00:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spell intercept?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.68,0:00:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An order to retreat?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.78,0:00:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Angelene.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.68,0:00:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.24,0:00:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:01:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how the largest Christian Church,\Nthe Roman Catholic Church, does their dirty work!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.52,0:01:07.23,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(762,493)\fad(1000, 1000)}#04 Sheol Fear\NDemon Killer's Voice
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.96,0:01:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If everything this man told us was true,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.45,0:01:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas will not be executed immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.41,0:01:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have their own circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.77,0:01:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.50,0:01:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The decryption of The Book of the Law may be a threat to the Roman Catholic Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.54,0:01:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Orsola Aquinas has never sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.31,0:01:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't simply murder believers of God's Gospel, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.73,0:01:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did the Amakusa Church try to stop Orsola's assassination?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.96,0:01:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.72,0:01:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"One may not murder a believer of God's Gospel."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.61,0:01:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An interpretation of this rule is that those who have been kicked out of the church
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.48,0:01:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can be murdered as non-believers of God's Gospel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.35,0:01:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, she'll bear the label "enemy of God."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:02:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power a grimoire contains cannot bring happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.71,0:02:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It brings about nothing but conflict to those around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.80,0:02:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid to say this, but it's already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.96,0:02:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's out of our hands now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.45,0:02:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.89,0:02:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you take a person's life for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This occurred within the Roman Catholic Church,\Nand they will judge the case with their own rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.95,0:02:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or could it be that you wish to save her, even if it means war?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid. Don't get so depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.33,0:02:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the Church of England,\Nwe have a huge reason to fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll invade their hideout and rescue Orsola along with our idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you plan on going alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.58,0:02:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the only option, then I have no choice but to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.21,0:03:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like it's been decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll split up and hide ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.94,0:03:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to Academy City with Index.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.29,0:03:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.41,0:03:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.00,0:03:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's one more thing I need to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.45,0:03:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.52,0:03:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That cross I gave you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.88,0:03:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem to have it with you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.65,0:03:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, I gave it to Orsola.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.67,0:03:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it expensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but its value was in you holding it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.36,0:03:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.19,0:03:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.61,0:04:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.29,0:04:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't there something I could've done?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a quarrel between magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to force yourself to get involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can solve every problem that appears before them by themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.16,0:04:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.86,0:04:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our fridge is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go find a convenience store and buy a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should all go together, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:04:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I run around, I'll eventually find one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.11,0:05:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Church of Orsola"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.77,0:05:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.97,0:05:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas managed to spread God's Gospel to three pagan countries
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and received special permission to construct a church bearing her own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, you shouldn't waste our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, we don't have the time to play around with your games.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.64,0:06:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you understand, shut up and accept your punishment—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.31,0:06:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.95,0:06:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you a question, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.06,0:06:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, it seems you don't have many friends to rely on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that you'd ask the Amakusa Church you had just met for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.09,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church, the Church of England...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ridiculous for those churches to even call themselves Christian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in this current state because you put your precious life in their filthy hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't take much to fool them and have them bring you to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.54,0:06:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... fooled...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fooled... them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.04,0:06:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.07,0:06:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... you weren't cooperating with them, but fooling them... instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.61,0:06:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.12,0:07:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're useless if you hand what you're supposed to protect to the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you smiling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.78,0:07:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... I'm actually smiling right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had an epiphany...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...as to what the Roman Catholic Church really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The others act based on their beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believing in people, and believing in their thoughts...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.46,0:07:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believing in those feelings, they will probably go to any lengths to pursue whatever they seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.58,0:07:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In comparison, all we do is act upon our doubts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.26,0:07:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how ugly is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you really want to die, then just get it over with!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.96,0:08:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, you should die\Ncursing those who brought you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.96,0:08:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.92,0:08:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...should I curse them for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.10,0:08:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They had no reason to fight in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.24,0:08:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, they came running for me, a stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.21,0:08:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything more wonderful than that in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.42,0:08:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've given me such a wonderful gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.93,0:08:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what exactly should I curse them for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way... the barrier was breached?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.58,0:09:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. Which organization did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.16,0:09:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering how a rookie could manage to do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.98,0:09:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems you have some sort of absolute power against the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.93,0:09:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.01,0:09:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you don't plan on fooling me again, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool you? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.90,0:09:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell from the situation? Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last I saw, the Church of England retreated, so what on Earth are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.80,0:09:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, this is your last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know very well what you should do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:09:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.79,0:10:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is indeed my last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.44,0:10:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard... what the hell do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.75,0:10:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me what I should do, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.03,0:10:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking me for a fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.73,0:10:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm obviously rescuing her!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can you do here, all by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.54,0:10:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you show us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.15,0:10:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just start things on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.35,0:10:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The Church of England?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.73,0:10:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible... this is an exclusive problem of the Roman Catholic Church!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.82,0:10:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you understand that this will be considered disruption of our internal affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.11,0:11:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, that is not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.14,0:11:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at Orsola Aquinas's chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There lies the cross of the Church of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.36,0:11:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By having someone put the necklace on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.79,0:11:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you gain protection from the Church of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Orsola Aquinas is no longer of the Roman Catholic Church, but of us, the Church of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.70,0:11:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.84,0:11:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think that sort of logic will work?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.43,0:11:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for you, the Roman Catholic Church,\Nto have sole discretion in her interrogation...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Church of England can't just stand back and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, how dare you point a weapon at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.05,0:11:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look like the kind of person who'd be kind and forgiving enough to let that go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.95,0:12:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because we're now against two instead of one—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go thinking this'll end with just two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.09,0:12:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you don't need to hear the reason why I'm fighting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.76,0:12:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatemiya...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had just finished conversing with the Church of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.44,0:12:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning on taking care of everything before you came, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're more stupid than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I dislike stupid people that are fun to watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even told you that I'd take care of things so you didn't have to worry, Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we have no choice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's rescue Orsola Aquinas, Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With our own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.95,0:13:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.91,0:13:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.01,0:13:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.72,0:13:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason to fight is so easy to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.65,0:13:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't be more thankful, grateful, and moved, huh, Kanzaki-neechin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.74,0:14:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuchimikado.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, isn't that dandy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You now know your old friends didn't kidnap Orsola in order to use The Book of the Law for their own interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.60,0:14:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.46,0:14:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fairly certain you had planned on using all this commotion to steal The Book of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.74,0:14:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you have a good idea of what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church didn't steal The Book of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.32,0:14:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a false accusation the Roman Catholic Church made.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.57,0:14:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It follows that there was no reason to bring the authentic Book of the Law to Japan, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.54,0:14:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Book of the Law that was brought to Japan was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.67,0:14:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm assuming the original still resides deep within the Vatican Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.35,0:14:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Are you satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.85,0:14:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. With them around...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.83,0:15:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church can walk down the correct path without my guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.52,0:15:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.10,0:15:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.61,0:16:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I not getting any action?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.04,0:16:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now isn't the time to approach her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her power will be weakened if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a song that uses the contents of all 103,000 grimoires to relentlessly expose the contradictions in their teachings:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sheol Fear."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For those who live their lives according to doctrine, you could call it their worst enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.09,0:17:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to it causes their spirits to temporarily crumble, much like a jigsaw puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.70,0:17:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grimoires are not just for reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.53,0:17:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can use those grimoires even though she has no magical abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.65,0:17:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There probably isn't anyone else more fit for the role of a grimoire library.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But man... why didn't you use a\Ntrump card like that from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.86,0:17:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That attack works on group mentality to pierce through mental barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the question then becomes,\N"how pure is this group mentality?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.00,0:18:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we fought against you, Kamijou and I acted as obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lowering the purity in which the chant could be activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd hate to get hit by the likes of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.25,0:18:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop being babies!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll look like idiots otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially you, Sister Angelene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.58,0:18:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But Sister Agnese, it's been over ten minutes since the battle began.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still outnumber them heavily even if we count Orsola with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.98,0:18:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.00,0:18:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which side caused that explosion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.79,0:18:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're going on the offensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.77,0:18:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let's fight as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.02,0:18:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need all the numbers we can get...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I relieve you of your position as my escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.94,0:19:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please go join the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes! We won't let them go, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't run...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way they can run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just how this damned world works...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Focus on attacking; do not worry about defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.05,0:19:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be prepared to die in order to defeat our Lord's enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.52,0:19:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that some sort of magical attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.81,0:20:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did that to avoid Sheol Fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:27.93,Preview,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.97,0:20:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final battle has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.94,0:20:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The avalanche of attacks has pushed us into a corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a way for us to emerge victorious?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.68,0:20:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time: "Lotus Wand."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.43,0:20:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When science and magic cross paths, this epic will begin!
